AU  - Caplin, Andrew S.
AU  - Spulber, Daniel F.
T1  - Menu Costs and the Neutrality of Money*
PY  - 1987
Y1  - 1987/11/01
DO  - 10.2307/1884277
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 102
IS  - 4
SP  - 703
EP  - 725
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - A model of endogenous price adjustment under money growth is presented. Firms follow (s,S) pricing policies, and price revisions are imperfectly synchronized. In the aggregate, price stickiness disappears, and money is neutral. The connection between firm price adjustment and relative price variability in the presence of monetary growth is also investigated. The results contrast with those obtained in models with exogenous fixed timing of price adjustment.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/1884277
ER  - 



